Portfolio Website

Responsive Portfolio Website using HTML & CSS

Description

This project is a beginner-friendly personal portfolio website built using HTML and CSS.
It includes the following sections:

Header & Navigation
Hero Section with Animated Text
About Me
Projects
Skills Table
Contact Form
Footer
Back to Top Button

The website uses Flexbox, CSS transitions, and animation effects.
It is fully responsive and adjusts smoothly across various screen sizes.

Steps to View Responsive Behavior

To test how the website adjusts on different screen sizes:
Open Developer Tools
Right-click → Inspect
Click the device toolbar icon (top-left in DevTools)
Test These Breakpoints (Manually Tested)

Device Type	Width Tested	Behavior
Mobile	320px – 480px	Sections stack vertically, text and buttons stay centered, hero image moves below text
Tablet	768px	Two-column areas compress nicely, navigation links stay aligned, hero keeps spacing
Small Laptop	1024px	Layout expands, grids align cleanly, image and text fit side-by-side
Desktop	1366px and above	Full-width layout with comfortable spacing, hero image and text remain properly aligned
Try Rotating (Landscape / Portrait)

This helps verify adaptive spacing, text wrapping, and card layout.

Resize Browser Window
Drag the browser edges to see smooth transitions for:
Grid cards
Navigation links
Hero alignment
Form fields

